               <p>234. (L.) 
               
                  <persName id="t17640502-12-defend121" type="defendantName">
                     Michael 
                     Sampson 
                  <interp inst="t17640502-12-defend121" type="surname" value="Sampson"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-defend121" type="given" value="Michael"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-defend121" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
               
            , <rs id="t17640502-12-deflabel56" type="occupation">Gent</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-12-defend121 t17640502-12-deflabel56"></join>. was indicted for <rs id="t17640502-12-off57" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-off57" type="offenceCategory" value="deception"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-off57" type="offenceSubcategory" value="forgery"></interp>
               forging and counterfeiting a certain bill of exchange, purporting to be drawn by Lord 
                     <persName id="t17640502-12-person122">
                        Adam 
                        Gordon 
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-person122" type="surname" value="Gordon"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-person122" type="given" value="Adam"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-person122" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , commonly called the Hon. Adam Gordon, directed to 
                     <persName id="t17640502-12-person123">
                        William 
                        Adair 
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-person123" type="surname" value="Adair"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-person123" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-person123" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     </persName>
                  , Esq; for the payment of 32 l. 10 s. and for publishing the same; and for forging and publishing an acceptance thereto, with intent to defraud 
                     
                        <persName id="t17640502-12-victim125" type="victimName">
                           Henry 
                           Baldero 
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-victim125" type="surname" value="Baldero"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-victim125" type="given" value="Henry"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t17640502-12-victim125" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-12-off57 t17640502-12-victim125"></join>
                     </persName>
                      
                   and <rs id="t17640502-12-viclabel58" type="occupation">Co</rs>
                     <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-12-victim125 t17640502-12-viclabel58"></join>
               
                  </rs>.</p>
               <p>To which he <rs id="t17640502-12-verdict59" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-verdict59" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-verdict59" type="verdictSubcategory" value="pleadedGuilty"></interp>
               pleaded Guilty
            </rs>. <rs id="t17640502-12-punish60" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17640502-12-punish60" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17640502-12-defend121 t17640502-12-punish60"></join>
               Death
            </rs>. </p>
